{"title":"About","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"About","format":"html"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nI am Jimmy Cloutier (JIM-EE KL-oo-tyeh), a data and investigative journalist at the [Pittsburgh Post-Gazette](https://www.post-gazette.com/). That's a fancy way of saying I get paid to sift through large datasets and records to find and tell stories in the public interest. \n\nBefore I joined the Post-Gazette, I covered campaign finance and lobbying for [OpenSecrets](https://www.opensecrets.org/), a nonprofit that tracks the influence of money in U.S. politics.I also freelanced for the [Virginia Center for Investigative Journalism](https://vcij.org/). \n\nI studied English literature at Virginia Commonwealth University and later graduated with a master's degree in investigative journalism from Arizona State University. Between then, I taught high school and spent two years in Armenia with the U.S. Peace Corps, teaching English as a foreign language. \n\nI grew up outside Richmond, Virginia, but I was born in a small town in Québec, Canada.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n::: column-body-left\n**Contact**\n\n[jcloutier\\@post-gazette.com](mailto:jcloutier@post-gazette.com){.email}\n\nYou can reach me securely through the encrypted messaging app [Signal](https://signal.org/) at **jrcloutier.92**.\n:::\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\nI am Jimmy Cloutier (JIM-EE KL-oo-tyeh), a data and investigative journalist at the [Pittsburgh Post-Gazette](https://www.post-gazette.com/). That's a fancy way of saying I get paid to sift through large datasets and records to find and tell stories in the public interest. \n\nBefore I joined the Post-Gazette, I covered campaign finance and lobbying for [OpenSecrets](https://www.opensecrets.org/), a nonprofit that tracks the influence of money in U.S. politics.I also freelanced for the [Virginia Center for Investigative Journalism](https://vcij.org/). \n\nI studied English literature at Virginia Commonwealth University and later graduated with a master's degree in investigative journalism from Arizona State University. Between then, I taught high school and spent two years in Armenia with the U.S. Peace Corps, teaching English as a foreign language. \n\nI grew up outside Richmond, Virginia, but I was born in a small town in Québec, Canada.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n::: column-body-left\n**Contact**\n\n[jcloutier\\@post-gazette.com](mailto:jcloutier@post-gazette.com){.email}\n\nYou can reach me securely through the encrypted messaging app [Signal](https://signal.org/) at **jrcloutier.92**.\n:::\n\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":"auto","echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"brand":{"brand":{"color":{"palette":{"white":"#FFFEF